MS SHAREPOINT DEVELOPER
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/01 09:08:12
Ref. JB3046221
Job Description
·
Translates requirements defined into logical and practical systems.
·
Participates in leading internal SharePoint projects.
·
Participates in the architectural design, development customization and integration efforts of solutions involving collaboration, portals, content management, and workflows.
·
Consults with the business on design and business value of portal solutions.
·
Ensure the follow of standards through development life cycle.
·
Apply new modifications for the up and running portal services.
·
Hands on problem solving related to programming issues.
·
Designs, develops, debugs, tests, deploys, maintains and documents SharePoint solutions using out of the box functionality when possible and custom code as needed. This includes web parts, InfoPath forms, templates, page layouts, and master pages.
·
Using SharePoint Designer to design, develop workflows, web parts and connect to external data sources.
·
Assists with the development and lifecycle evolution of standards, guidelines and principles while ensuring best practices, standards, and security strategies are followed.
·
Defining requirements for improving or replacing systems.
·
Verify services to meet requirements.
·
Analyze and troubleshoot problems and recommend solutions, escalate as necessary.
·
Ensure Operational Procedures and Documentation are updated and well maintained.
·
Self-starter, motivated, proactive and able to learn new skills quickly
·
Has to possess good English communication skills (written as well as spoken)
·
Communicate courteously with all customers (internal and external) by telephone and email building positive relationships.
·
Attend or provide training/meetings whenever required
Skills
The candidate must meet the following criteria:
·
Bsc. in Computer Science.
·
Five (5) years of progressive experience latest SharePoint; dot net development.
·
Microsoft Certified Professional Developer (MCPD) SharePoint Developer.
·
Microsoft Certified Technical Specialist Certification (MCTS) for .Net.
·
Experience in business workflows with an understanding of the capabilities of Microsoft Office SharePoint Server, and SharePoint Designer.
·
Experience integration third party workflows such as K2, NINTEX.
·
Experience Creating Custom SharePoint Site and List Definitions.
·
Experience Building/Implementing Custom SharePoint Workflows.
·
Editing Sites in SharePoint Designer.
·
Experience in developing and implementing Web Parts.
·
Experience using Visual Studio (TFS / SourceSafe).
·
Experience in Integration with Active Directory.
·
Strong experience with Microsoft .Net
and above, C#, .
·
Experience using T-SQL, XML, XSLT, CAML, AJAX, JQuery, HTML, JavaScript,CSS.
·
Experience in , Multi-Threading, .Net Remoting, IIS, Windows Services, Web Services and SOAP technology.
·
Strong experience in writing reusable components.
·
Experience Silverlight, WCF, Entity Framework and LINQ.
·
Mobile Application development is plus.
·
Experience with Power shell scripts would be a plus.
·
Good interpersonal, management, communication skills and problem Solving.
·
Must speak, read and write both English and (Arabic Natively).
·
Saudi is preferred.
